	<tr>
	  <td width='100%' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' align='center'>UNYIELDING WISH: THE BEGINNING</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%'><font face='verdana' size='2pt'><html>

<head>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=windows-1252">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 4.0">
<meta name="ProgId" content="FrontPage.Editor.Document">
<title>New Page 1</title>
</head>

<body>
<font SIZE="2">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b>~*Unyielding Wish: The Beginning*~</b></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> </p>
<p class="MsoNormal">   <span style="mso-tab-count: 1">           
</span>Alielle took a deep
breath and stepped outside.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The air
around her was crisp and cool, as it usually was on a typical morning in the
tree city of Kelethin.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She closed
her eyes and took a few breaths of the sweet air and listened to the happy
chirping of the birds.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Pleased with
her surroundings, Alielle picked up her backpack and began to set off toward the
Ranger guild.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Today seemed a day just like any other to most, but it was very special
to Alielle.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Today she was going to
be given her primary long-term assignment.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>It seemed as though she had waited for this time to come since the day
her parents brought her through the doors of Faydark's Champions.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Alielle was so excited that she began skipping up and down the ramps and
across the platforms as she navigated toward her guild.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Her skipping turned in to sprinting when she could see the roof of the
building.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She screeched to a halt
right in front of the doors.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Slightly
out of breath, Alielle tugged on the doorknob of the large door before her but
it would not open.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She peeked
inside the window and couldn't see anyone in there.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Where was everyone, she wondered?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Slightly
disappointed, Alielle sat down next to where she had dropped her backpack near
the doors.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She looked slightly
perplexed with a small pout and her brow furrowed gently.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>While lost in thought, Alielle didn't notice the figure walking toward
her.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The figure stood right next to
her, but Alielle paid no mind.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>However,
her reverie was interrupted by the sound of laughter.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>She blinked her eyes and looked around; standing practically
over her was her guild leader chuckling away.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Leader!" cried Alielle as she scampered to her feet and stood
at attention.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Composing himself, Maesyn Trueshot, the respected leader of the Rangers
guild said playfully, "Here I thought I was getting here early today.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Tell me, Ms. Taallis, how long have you been here?"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Alielle looked slightly embarrassed and looked around nervously, tapping
her fingertips together.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>"I'm
not sure," was the quick reply, then a pause.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>After deeper thought, "Um, maybe a half hour?"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>He laughed again and patted Alielle on the head.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>"You're too adorable!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I
might just have to cancel your mission just to keep you here.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>I couldn't think of anyone who could possibly replace your positive
attitude and excitement."<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>He
beamed a smile at her and unlocked the door to the building.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>"Now let's go in and wait for the others," he said and led
Alielle inside.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Waiting for the others proved to be harder than she thought.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>She waited on a bench by the wall, fidgeting nervously.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She had to smile though because it reminded her so much of the first time
she'd come to the guild.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She was
still very young when her parents decided that they would let her begin her
formal instruction.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She had been
trying to convince them for years that she should begin training.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Alielle idolized her older brothers and wanted nothing more than to be
strong like them.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>They had all been
training at the Ranger's guild for several years.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>Her mother warned her brothers, Satoru, Masaru and Kakeru, to
keep an eye on her and make sure she didn't get hurt.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>They replied with the usual, "Oh, we'd NEVER let
anything happen to our dear little sister!"<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>But they weren't lying.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>In
truth they were very protective of her.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>It was too bad that they couldn't be here for this day.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Each of them was already away on their own assignment.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Her father, too, was on a training mission, but she knew they would all
be proud of her.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Just then, Maesyn
Trueshot walked up and touched Alielle on the shoulder.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She looked up and he smiled at her.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Are you nervous?" he inquired.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>She forced a smile, "No, of course not!"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"It's all right if you are.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I
might think you weren't normal if you weren't!" he jested.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>"I remember when I was first put on my assignment, I was
so nervous my knees were knocking together!"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"You had an assignment?" Alielle asked in disbelief.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>He chuckled, "Of course I did.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Did you think I just asked to be the guild leader?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>No, dear girl, I earned it.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I
succeeded my master before me.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Who
knows, maybe one day you will take over for me."<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Do you think so?"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Time will tell.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>However,
that's enough chitchat to get your mind off of the task at hand.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>Now it's time to go!"<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>He grabbed her hand and pulled her off of the bench.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>He opened the doors to the Great room and guided her to the very center.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>People were gathered on the sides, looking directly at her.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>Her guild mates were there, the trainers, her mother, and
other various people who came to watch.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She
could feel all the eyes on her and began fidgeting again.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She caught sight of her mother, who was motioning for her to stand still
and stop acting so nervous.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>Alielle straightened up and stood at attention, looking
straight ahead though she could still feel the butterflies in her stomach.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Alielle Taallis," began Maesyn Trueshot, "You have been
brought before everyone today to be given the assignment for your long term
mission.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>This mission is designed
to help shape Norrath in to a beautiful world in the name of our mother, Tunare.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Not everyone will complete their assignment, and some may lose their life
in the line of duty.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>Are you aware of the risks involved and are you prepared to
lay down your life for Tunare?"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Alielle projected her reply through the room, "I know I may face
many dangers in my journey; I am prepared.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>I would willingly give my life for those I love in the name of our
mother, Tunare!"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Let it be known, that Alielle has completed all the training
necessary to begin work on the Greater Mission.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>However, is there anyone present who would protest this?"<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>He paused for a moment, "Then I decree that Alielle
Taallis has now obtained the rank of Ranger and is no longer an Apprentice
Ranger."<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>He smiled at her from
the front of the room while people began to applaud.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>She was feeling slightly less nervous now.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>After the applause died down he began again, "Alielle, your
assignment is to spread the word of Tunare and to protect the animals of Norrath
from those who would seek to destroy them.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>To try to bring peace and understanding to all people and to uphold the
honor of Faydark's Champions.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Do
you accept this mission?"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"I do!"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Do you have anything you would like to say?"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Yes, sir, I do."<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Then please say it in the presence of this audience."<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Alielle took a deep breath and began, "I have a wish that I have
held in my heart since as long as I can remember.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>My wish is to save, our world, Norrath.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>We are killing ourselves with the violence and trickery we impose upon
ourselves.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The malicious acts of a
few have lived on and undermined the trust of others.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>The world is consumed by fear and hatred.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>The teachings of Cazic Thule and Innoruuk run rampant and poison the
hearts of a profound majority.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Many
people may not even realize that they have accepted hatred unto themselves.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"But we can change this sad fate.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>If we all work together to try to be kind to one another, we have a
chance.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Cruelty begets cruelty, but
kindness breeds more kindness.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>If
we give ourselves selflessly to others, we will find that they will be willing
to help us when we are in need.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>If
we try, then we can finally rebuild the trust that has been lost.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-tab-count:1">            
</span>"We should not be using our weapons and skills
to destroy and cause pain to others.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>We
should, instead, use them to protect the ones we love; the sword that protects.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"This is my dream; to see all people, regardless of race or
religion, united through friendship and love.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>I will fight for what I believe in; I can't lose heart.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>I will never stop, never falter.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I
will remain determined until the day that this, my unyielding wish, comes
true."<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Maesyn Trueshot looked proudly at Alielle and then spoke, "Your
wisdom belies your age, child.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>We
wish you luck in your journeys and will pray for the day that your wish comes
true.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>May Tunare guide you."<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Cheers and applause roared up in the room.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>The people who had stood along the sides now moved in all around Alielle
and congratulated her.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Many of her
guild mates came up and expressed how happy they were for her.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>After all, it was a big step to go from Apprentice Ranger to Ranger,
which required a lot of training and study.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She began to feel more at ease and the nervousness faded completely.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She gave her mother a big hug and then ran up to her mentor and guild
leader.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>People continued talking and celebrating in the background as Alielle
stared at Maesyn Trueshot.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>He had
been so kind to her all these years.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Tears
began to well up in her eyes and she began, "I'll miss..."<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"I know," he interrupted, "But I have faith in you!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>I know you'll succeed and bring honor to our guild.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Just promise me you'll come back to visit from time to time."<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>He reached out and wiped the tears from her eyes.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Of course I will!"<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She
grasped his hand and looked at him, suddenly very serious.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>"I will not fail you, leader!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I...I'll
do everything I can to make you proud of me.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>You'll see, I'll never give up!"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"I know," he whispered and pulled her in for a great big bear
hug.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>"Now go enjoy the
celebration!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>We're celebrating you,
you know!"<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>He turned her
around and they both walked toward the crowd of people.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> ------------------------------------------------------------<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Alielle collapsed on to her bed.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She
had a great time at the ceremony and the celebration that followed.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Between that and all the preparations she had to make, her day was
entirely filled up.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>It was dark
outside now and she was exhausted.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>She crawled under her blankets and nodded off to sleep.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Tomorrow would be an even bigger day than today.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Tomorrow she would leave home to set off on her mission.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> ------------------------------------------------------------<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Morning came entirely too soon.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Alielle
was still fast asleep when her mother came in to her room to wake her.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Ali, honey, wake up.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>You're
going to be late!"<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Her mother
shook her until she was conscious. <o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-tab-count:1">            
</span>Alielle's eyes snapped open, "Oh no!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Mom, what time is it!?"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"The sun has been up for more than an hour."<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Alielle ran around her room, getting dressed, making final preparations,
packing a few last minute things.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She
picked up all her supplies and ran for the door.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She looked at her mother, "Mom..."<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"I know, dear.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I'll be
down at the guild in a minute."<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Satisfied, Alielle burst out of the house and started sprinting toward
the Ranger guild.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She tore through
the city, trying to be careful not to bump in to any of the other people and
accidentally knock them from the platforms.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She ran past the bank and headed straight off the edge of the platform.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She jumped as high in to the air as she could and hoped for the best.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She rolled as she managed to land on the platform the Ranger guild
resided on.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Coming out of the roll,
Alielle took the last few steps toward the building.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She arrived just as Maesyn Trueshot opened the doors. <o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Ah, perfect timing, like usual!" chimed the guild leader,
taking note of her heavy breathing and chuckling to himself.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Did...I...<cough> make it...on time?" panted Alielle.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"But of course!"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Oh...good...<cough>" she smiled brightly.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Once inside, Maesyn Trueshot handed Alielle a map, a journal, and some
armor and weapons.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She went to
change in to her new armor.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Her mother
had arrived by the time she was done.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Oh honey, you look great!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Green
has always been such a lovely color on you," her mother came up and hugged
Alielle as she spoke.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Alielle
turned to face her guild leader.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Well, what do you think?" she implored him.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"You look fantastic!" he said with a grin, but then furrowed
his brow.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>"There's something
wrong though...let's see here, what could it be?"<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>He put his hand on his chin and studied Alielle.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>"Ah ha!" he cried when it dawned on him, "It's your helm.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>It doesn't suit you one bit and covers up your pretty face."<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"I wasn't going to say anything," said Alielle's mother.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"I think I have just the thing." The guild leader went to the
supply room and rummaged around.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>"Here
it is!"<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>He came back out
toward Alielle with a leather looking cap.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>He helped her to put it on, then took a step back to look.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>"There, that's much better!"<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Alielle's mother agreed with him and Alielle jumped up and down in
delight.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Several more preparations were made, and soon it was time to set off.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Alielle, her mother, and Maesyn Trueshot all walked off toward the lifts.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Once down on the ground, Alielle turned to them.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>She looked lovingly at her mother, "I'll miss you so much, mom!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>You've done such a great job raising Satoru, Masaru, Kakeru and
I.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I know I was sometimes a
handful, but I just want you to know that I love you with all my heart!"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"I know, Ali.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I love
you, too," her mother assured as they hugged.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Alielle then turned to her mentor.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Sir, I want to thank you too.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>You were always so nice to me and helped me whenever I needed it.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>I feel like you're more than just my guild leader; I feel like you're my
friend, too.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>So thank you!"<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She grabbed him and embraced him.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>He hugged her back and patted her on the head.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>"I will miss you, Alielle.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>You
always knew how to brighten my day.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>It
was a pleasure helping you, and I hope you won't be a stranger.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>I will be here if you need help, so don't be afraid to call on me."<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Alielle smiled at him, "I won't!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>I'll miss you too, Maesyn Trueshot!"<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She stood there, not wanting the moment to end.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Knowing that the next step was to leave the ones she held so dear.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She took a deep breath and said, "I guess I'll be off then."<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>The pair smiled at her and took turns hugging her.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>They said good-bye to her and she turned to leave.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>"Good-bye!<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>I will miss you!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>But
don't worry, I'll come back!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I love
you!"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>She walked down the path, away from the ones she loved, looking back
every now and then to wave.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She was
sad to go, but was filled with a sense of excitement.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Alielle reminded herself that she had waited for this day to come and it
was finally here.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Her dragging
footsteps became more resolute and soon she was well on her way.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>Whistling a little tune to herself, Alielle meandered through the forest
of the Faydark toward the Butcherblock Mountains.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She'd decided that the best place to start her work would be on the main
continent of Antonica, so she hoped to catch a boat from the port at the edge of
the mountains to the coastal city of Freeport.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> ------------------------------------------------------------<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>The forest was quiet, save for the rustling of the trees and the sounds
of animals.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Suddenly, the peace was
shattered by a piercing scream.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Alielle
perked up and turned the direction the scream came from.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She ran several hundred yards in that direction as fast as she could
until she came upon the scene.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She
saw two Dark Elves and a Troll standing there with frightened looking, leather
clad Wood Elf in their possession.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Without
hesitation, Alielle ran straight in to the fray.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"What's going on here?!" demanded Alielle.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>The attention was turned from the captive, young Druid to Alielle.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>A Dark Elf, encased in silver plated armor leered at her and spoke,
"Why, we were just having a conversation with our little friend,
here."<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Yah!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Liddul frend!"
mimicked the Troll, who was holding the Druid with his massive arms.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She winced slightly.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Then why did she scream?" Alielle motioned to the Wood Elf.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>The other Dark Elf piped up, she was scantily clad in a fine chain armor
that left little to the imagination, "Well, you see, saw a giant wasp.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She doesn't like insects."<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Is that true?" Alielle asked the other Wood Elf.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"No, they..." the Troll quickly covered the Druid's mouth.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Of course it's true," interjected the plated Dark Elf.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>"There's not going to be a problem, is there?"<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>He reached up and tapped his hand lightly on the hilt of his sword.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"I don't want to fight you, but I don't think she wants to be here
at all.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Please, let's talk about
this.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>If you refuse to let her go
I...I'll be forced to challenge you!" Alielle said uncertainly.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She set her pack down and pulled her weapons out.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She grasped the sharp claws she used as a weapon with her right hand and
uncurled her whip with the other.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>The male Dark Elf walked toward her and drew his massive two-handed blade
from the scabbard across his back.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Alielle
looked to the side of him and saw the female pull a dagger from behind her back
as well as one from her boot.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The
Troll let go of the girl, who scampered up a small rise and watched from behind
a tree.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>He then picked up a large,
ornate staff and began chanting softly.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She
turned her attention back to the silvery Dark Elf who now was only a few feet
from her.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>He was staring directly
at her with a look that seemed to pierce her very soul.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>He had an evil grin on his face while he watched her squirm
uncomfortably under his gaze. <o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"My name is Mallecus, I am a Dark Knight of my Lord Innoruuk.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>My lovely friend behind me is Xeilora, and the large one is Grug.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Might I know your name before I kill you, light one?"<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"A...Alielle.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>My name
is Alielle."<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Very well then, Alielle.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Here
I come!"<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>With that Mallecus
took the remaining steps between them and slashed at her with his sword.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>Alielle quickly did a few handsprings backwards to dodge the
attack.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>She straightened herself
and got in a fighting stance.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"I don't want to fight you, Mallecus!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Please, can't we just talk to each other to find a solution?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Fighting is not the answer," pleaded Alielle.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"There will be no talk...only blood!" cried Mallecus, a dark
aura surrounding his hand.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>"I'asuka..."
the energy quickly flared up and formed a ball in his hand, which he raised
above his head as it grew bigger, "...CH'O!"<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>The ball of energy leapt from his hand and toward Alielle.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span><o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>The aura coming from the attack left Alielle paralyzed with fear.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>It had a strange sense about it that was unfamiliar, yet very strong.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>She tried to move, but couldn't; her feet seemingly rooted to the ground.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Instinct took over and she closed her eyes, folded her arms across her
chest and said a small prayer.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Her
skin quickly hardened and she braced for the impact.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>It all happened in an instant.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>The dark energy hit its mark, creating a large cloud of dirt and debris.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Mallecus turned to his companions and laughed heartily.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"Well then, where were we?" he asked as if nothing had
happened.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>"Ah yes, the girl.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Grug, go bring her back."<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Grug
turned and walked toward the scared Elf.<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="mso-tab-count:1">           
</span>"We're not finished yet!" came a voice from behind him.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"> </p>
<p class="MsoNormal">To be continued...</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Next Chapter: The Journey</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-tab-count:1"><br>
</span></p>
